Description: 
Examining how Britain has influenced musical theatre 
across the world, after overcoming American domination 
of the West End after the Second World War. The first 
edition also explores the successful partnership between 
Tim Rice and Andrew Lloyd Webber. Featuring 
contributions by the former collaborators, as well as 
Cameron Mackintosh, Elaine Paige, Ron Moody, Bill 
Kenwright, Sheila Hancock, Harold Prince, Robert 
Stigwood, Tommy Steele, Paul Nicholas and Willy 
Russell.
